Fortune Teller
This simple Python script, titled "Fortune Teller," allows you to ask the fortune teller a question and receive a random fortune in response. The fortune is determined by rolling a random number between 1 and 9.

How to Use
Run the Script: Execute the Python script in your preferred environment.

Start the Fortune Teller: Press enter to start the fortune teller.

Ask a Question: Think of a question you would like to ask the fortune teller, then press enter to continue.

Reveal Your Fortune: The fortune teller will think for a moment, then press enter again to reveal your fortune.

View the Fortune: The fortune teller will display your fortune based on the random number rolled.

Play Again: After receiving your fortune, you have the option to ask another question. Type "yes" to ask another question or "no" to exit.

Requirements
Python 3.x
random module
os module
Usage
python
Copy code
python fortune_teller.py
Note
This script works on both Windows and Unix/Linux-based systems, thanks to the os module used for clearing the console screen.
Ensure you have the required Python modules installed (random, os) before running the script.
